="" src="https://i.imgur.com/b5NvyxT.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Pzaiiq0</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[HiAlchemist]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It's been long enough, time to cut the shit.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/1DIJrBF</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5d00t3J.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I've been working on myself for a long time.  I quit drinking 5 years ago but weed (edibles) has always been a crutch for me.  The problem is I'm a "0/100" kinda guy: I don't know how to do ANYTHING in moderation.  So for a long time I've been eating my edibles on a daily basis, literally planning my days and weekends around it.  And the worst part? I've been doing it behind my wife and kids backs: they had no idea I was completely stoned all these years (I finally shared my need to compartmentalize due to a rough childhood with my therapist and this is part of it).

Well, I'm almost 45 and, well, it's been taking a toll on my professional productivity and if there's one thing I won't stand for it's my career taking a hit (get it: "taking a hit"?!!!....GET IT?!!!).  So I finished my edibles last week and I refuse to go buy more, and folks I think this is it.

The future is a bit stressful for me.  A fair percentage of my cannabis use was to numb myself from a few things I didn't want to address.  One example is my wife and kids (sounds bad, but hear me out): my wife - whom I love very much - is an extreme introvert and homebody, and well, I'm a social butterfly.  Being stoned all the time has allowed me to avoid being angry at a low activity and barely social lifestyle.  So I am worried that there will be some conflict in the future but right now I need to keep focused on myself.

Anyway, I've been feeling great and am hoping I can finally shed this dependency in conjunction with ending the lying to my family.  I think I can.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/1DIJrBF</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DamnedIfYouDo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>SATURDAY'S  100%  TRUTH</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Hxe62e9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rdAyQjn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Hxe62e9</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[doxydad1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It's been so many years.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/u6T8FJh</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ChKqzzF.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Having suffered from recurring depression and PTSD for over 20 years, it still sucks just as bad.
While it still sucks as bad as ever, the years of experience has made it easier to endure.
While the suicidal thoughts are there, I'm no longer a threat to myself as I once was.

It might not seem like much, but it's something that I'm proud of.

The only person in my life that knows the state of my mental health is my wife.
Not because I've told her, but because she knows me that well.

Edit:
Just a mental health vent.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/u6T8FJh</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Snowbourne]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Rock and Roar: From Stone to Majesty</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XJ97o7o</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kY4LA2h.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XJ97o7o</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Smadyined]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Oh my heart.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/s7wfXSG</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ollG0Af.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Rest in peace to both of you legends.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/s7wfXSG</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Discoball10]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Shannon Tweed</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/G09k3zz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TQWu7c5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1985</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/A9dgDrK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6hwfNx5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kN98BKD.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1983</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/G09k3zz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ngugi]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>